hulea\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/35533014?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alinhulea","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alinhulea\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/alinhulea","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alinhulea\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM1NTMzMDE0","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alinhulea\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alinhulea\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alinhulea\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"alinhulea","type":"User","id":35533014,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alinhulea\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/alinhulea\/orgs"}},{"index":13,"author_association":"NONE","body":"I have tried the webgl_test_memory example as it is and the memory seems to be released properly. \r\nHowever, using the canvas size of about 1000X1000 instead of 256X256 in the same example in Firefox will result in GPU memory greater that 3GB in a matter of seconds ...and crash\r\n\r\nTried the solution with a single POT canvas and it seems to work better, no crash.\r\nHowever the single POT canvas solution is not usable when multiple textures are created in a single frame, because all of the created textures share the same \"image\" reference at the point the texture is uploaded to the GPU. \r\nIf you can force the texture upload when creating it immediately then the single POT canvas solution could work, given that you do not need to re-upload the texture, as it would use the current canvas content not the initial one uploaded","created_at":"2018-01-25T12:27:24.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12469#issuecomment-360452552","id":360452552,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12469","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2MDQ1